    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n#35450 breaks diff3-style git mergetool using nvim.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nAssume that merge conflict occurs in the third line of a.txt:\n\n```\n--- a/a.txt\n+++ b/a.txt\n@@@ -1,5 -1,5 +1,11 @@@\n  # head\n\n++<<<<<<< HEAD\n +LOCAL\n++||||||| parent of 12345\n++BASE\n++=======\n+ REMOTE\n++>>>>>>> 12345\n\n  # EOF\n```\n\nThe files are archived in [a.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/22004252/a.zip).\nNow try to resolve it by git mergetool:\n\n```sh\nunzip a.zip\n# diff3-style mergetool\nnvim --clean \"set hidden | leftabove split | leftabove vertical split | 1b | wincmd l | leftabove vertical split | 2b | wincmd l | 3b | wincmd j | 4b | execute 'tabdo windo diffthis' | tabfirst\" a_LOCAL.txt a_BASE.txt a_REMOTE.txt a.txt\n```\n\nthen `jj1do` gives\n\n```\n# head\n\nLOCAL\n||||||| parent of 12345\nBASE\n=======\nREMOTE\n>>>>>>> 12345\n\n# EOF\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`jj1do` must give\n\n```\n# head\n\nLOCAL\n\n# EOF\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-117b129\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.1623\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty 1.1.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
